data.description:
Welcome to 114 Eden Creek Lane, a stunning 4-bedroom, 3-bathroom home with an oversized 3-car garage and a spacious office or den, nestled in the charming community of The Oaks of Indian River just off the sparkling blue Intracoastal waterway. This exquisite property, built in 2017 features CBS construction, Impact windows throughout, a picturesque backyard with sparkling blue pool and sits on a half acre of land making it a true gem in today's real estate market!As you pull up to your half-acre oasis, you will be amazed by the Key West style CBS home with a large paver driveway and lush Florida landscaping. Step inside, and you will notice the wide open floor plan as well as the detailed crown molding throughout your main living spaces. As you enter, you have a spacious dining room that seamlessly flows into your main living area and kitchen. Your main living area has large glass sliding doors that overlook your serene backyard, sparkling pool and large covered patio.

The heart of this home is the spacious kitchen, a perfect space for entertaining and culinary adventures. It features two toned wood cabinetry with ample storage space, sleek granite countertops, and a unique copper sink that adds a touch of character to the space. The brand new (2022) stainless steel LG appliances will ensure that you have the latest and greatest technology at your fingertips. 

Your primary suite is the perfect place to unwind after a long day, with views of the intracoastal waterway and a set of sliding glass doors leading out to your covered patio and picturesque backyard. Complete with a walk-in closet and a spa-like en-suite bathroom that features a walk-in shower, dual sinks, and a built-in vanity, to make getting ready for the day a breeze! 

You also have three other spacious bedrooms and two additional guest bathrooms. Additionally, you have a large laundry room with ample storage and counter space. Also, you have a large bonus room that can be used as an office, den, or playroom -  providing a versatile space for work or relaxation.

The fully fenced-in backyard is truly a tropical paradise and the ultimate entertainment space that will make your Sunday's at home feel like a day at a resort. Featuring views of the peaceful blue Intracoastal waters, an expansive covered patio with coffered wood ceiling and fans, screened-in sparkling blue pool and lush landscaping throughout. It is the perfect place to enjoy the  Florida sunshine and create lasting memories with friends and loved ones.
Additional features include a metal roof and impact glass windows and doors to ensure that your investment remains protected and energy-efficient for years to come. The property is also equipped with a 500-gallon in-ground propane tank, adding a level of convenience and versatility that is hard to find.

Location is key, and this home is ideally situated. You're just a short drive away from the vibrant downtown area of Jensen Beach, offering a wide range of dining, shopping, and entertainment options. Plus, you can be on the beautiful beaches of Hutchinson Island in less than 5 minutes, allowing you to soak up the sun, surf, and sea breeze whenever you desire.

Don't miss this opportunity to make 114 Eden Creek Lane your dream home. With its modern amenities, durable construction, and prime location, it's a rare find that won't last long. Schedule your private showing and make this beautiful property your new oasis in paradise.
